subSubSection.paragraph:
Chthonius gallettii
differs from
C. caoduroi
in the following main characters: anterior margin of carapace with 2 preocular microsetae on each side (1 preocular microseta in
C. caoduroi
); tergite I with 4 setae (2 or 3 setae in
C. caoduroi
); male chela length 1.52 mm , 7.4 times as long as deep ( 1.28–1.30 mm , 6.7–6.8 times as long as deep in
C. caoduroi
); fixed and movable chelal fingers in male with 70 and 50 teeth respectively (66–71 and 39–43 in
C. caoduroi
).
